<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Jensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">There should be clothing that would go along with the whole Gandalf wizard thing.  Big pointy purple hats with suns, moons and stars on them (horseshoes, clovers, and diamonds as well, j/k).  Complete the ensemble with a matching floor-length robe and you're set.  The cloaks would be magical of course with cool perks, that only people with high wizarding skills, like archane lore, could use. <P>I've seen the cloaks around, seems to be a seasonal thing, I'd just like to see more of it for wizards/witches :P<P>------------------<BR>You don't know the half of it...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Sir_Halken</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I was a little disappointed with the robes they put in. They seemed to have no other purpose than looks! Ya, I know item mages can enchant them and get al all over in one spell...but the robes should come with slight al, have more of them..and magic spells on them. I'd like to see them a normal loot item, with semi random<BR> stats and spells like the rest of the armor.<P>------------------<BR>Halken the Bold<BR>Guardians of Dereth Monarch<BR>Harvestgain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Heiji Kogatana</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">The new patch has brought an even larger emparassment to the Wizard profession. Slightly better than the old ones, apart from the fact that they make you look like a radioactive construction worker and drain 2 points of mana every second. Yes I've heard of the master robes, and even they don't have a base AL for times when mana stones are hard to come by.<BR>   Whatever happened to plain old red or black robes? Sure, the Matty robe looked good, but suddenly every third person I see has one on. I guess every new patch brings a new robe, however flawed it be.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Heiji Kogatana<BR>Mighty Mage of Morningthaw</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">DungeonCrawler</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I could dig a nice hooded black robe.   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>I think it's cool that they keep putting new stuff in.  I can see getting the apprentice robes if you're a newbie mage.  Also the mastery robes, maybe for more experienced mages to wear while trying to learn new spells or something.  Since they debuff all magics but one, it would be hard from someone like my mage to use (all four schools) but I still think they're neat.<P>Besides, if they didn't debuff, the non-mages would be complaining about them!   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>Just thought of this... part of the purpose in these robes might have been to steer mages away from wearing so much armor and back to more typical mage-type clothing.<P>I would have liked to have seen them have a little bit of armor to them.  Those mastery robes cost something like 50k, I think.<P>Sorry about the broken, stream-of-consciousness natyure of this post.  Kind of in a hurry!   <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Goth Shadowsun, War/Life/Creature/Item Mage<BR>Morningthaw</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Frantoll</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Here's a silly question, but if I don't ask now it will seem sillier.<P>1. What does "debuff" mean?<P>2. Actually, what does "buff" mean?  I thought "buff" meant casting a spell on someone that temporarily raised their attributes or skills.  But I've seen it used different ways.<P>3. And about these robes, the ones I looked at said they would cast certain "ineptitude" skills on the user?  Why would anyone in their right mind wear something like that?  I know I'm missing something, and I bet the answer to my first question will throw light on the third.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Sir_Halken</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Well, I haven't actually IDed the new robes...but from the sounds of it, they debuff (subtract skill) in all areas but one, which is buffed (add skill). So if you specialize in one area, it could be useful.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Halken the Bold<BR>Guardians of Dereth Monarch<BR>Harvestgain</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
